            "title": "Republic of the Congo: TotalEnergies Makes a Hydrocarbon Discovery on the Moho License",
            "id": "e9c70dc7-d00a-4a21-bafa-11e9e9b163bc",
            "description": "In Paris, TotalEnergies EP Congo, with a 63.5% stake as the operator, has reported a significant hydrocarbon discovery on the Moho license in the Republic of the Congo. This follows the successful drilling of the MHNM-6 NFW exploration well, which specifically targeted the Moho G structure. The well revealed a substantial hydrocarbon column of around 160 meters within high-quality Albian reservoirs. An extensive data collection and sampling initiative were conducted to facilitate subsurface analysis and guide future development efforts for the Moho G area.",
